        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 6:18PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 618 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Wadesboro, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wadesboro, Morven, McFarlan, and Diggs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
